# Tests of the gocdk-runtimevar program.

# We can't test watch in this test framework, because it runs indefinitely in the
# foreground. We would need to add some job control (background, kill). Probably
# not worth it.

$ gocdk-runtimevar cat constant://?val=foo&decoder=string
(string) foo

$ echof fvar contents

$ gocdk-runtimevar cat file:///${ROOTDIR}/fvar?decoder=string
(string) contents

$ go gocdk-runtimevar watch file:///${ROOTDIR}/fvar?decoder=string
$ sleep 1
$ echof fvar new contents
$ sleep 1
$ stop
Watching "file:///${ROOTDIR}/fvar?decoder=string" for changes...

(string) contents

(string) new contents


